{"info": {"author": "Tim Kamanin", "author_email": "tim@timonweb.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Environment :: Web Environment", "Framework :: Django", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries", "Topic :: Utilities"], "description": "# The integration of Tailwind CSS framework with Django a.k.a. Django + Tailwind = \u2764\n\n## Quick start\n\n1. Install the python package django-tailwind from pip\n\n   `pip install django-tailwind`\n\n   Alternatively, you can download or clone this repo and run `pip install -e .`.\n\n2. Add `tailwind` to INSTALLED_APPS in **settings.py**\n\n3. Create a tailwind-compatible Django-app, I like to call it `theme`:\n\n   `python manage.py tailwind init theme`\n\n4. Add your newly created `theme` app to INSTALLED_APPS in **settings.py**\n\n5. In settings.py, register tailwind app by adding the following string:\n\n   `TAILWIND_APP_NAME = 'theme'`\n\n6. Run a command to install all necessary dependencies for tailwind css:\n\n   `python manage.py tailwind install`\n\n7. Now, go and start tailwind in dev mode:\n\n   `python manage.py tailwind start`\n\n8. Django Tailwind comes with a simple `base.html` template that can be found under\n   `yourtailwindappname/templates/base.html`. You can always extend it or delete it if you\n   have own layout.\n\n9. If you're not using `base.html` template provided with Django Tailwind, add `styles.min.css` to your own `base.html` template file:\n\n   ```html\n   <link\n     rel=\"stylesheet\"\n     href=\"{% static 'css/styles.min.css' %}\"\n     type=\"text/css\"\n   />\n   ```\n\n10) You should now be able to use Tailwind CSS classes in your html.\n\n11) To build a production version of CSS run:\n\n    `python manage.py tailwind build`.\n\n## NPM executable path configuration\n\nSometimes (especially on Windows), Python executable can't find `NPM` installed in the system.\nIn this case, you need to set `NPM` executable path in settings.py file manually (Linux/Mac):\n\n```python\nNPM_BIN_PATH = '/usr/local/bin/npm'\n```\n\nOn windows it might look like:\n```python\nNPM_BIN_PATH = r\"C:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\npm.cmd\"\n```\n\nPlease note that `NPM` path of your system may be different. Try to run `which npm` in your\ncommand line to get the path.\n\n## Bugs and suggestions\n\nIf you have found a bug, please use the issue tracker on GitHub.\n\n[https://github.com/timonweb/django-tailwind/issues](https://github.com/timonweb/django-tailwind/issues)\n\n2020 (c) [Tim Kamanin - A Full Stack Django Developer](https://timonweb.com)\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/timonweb/django-tailwind", "keywords": "django,tailwind,css", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "django-tailwind", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/django-tailwind/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/django-tailwind/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/timonweb/django-tailwind"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/django-tailwind/0.7.1/", "requires_dist": ["django (>=2.2,<3.1)"], "requires_python": ">=3.6,<3.9", "summary": "Tailwind CSS Framework for Django projects", "version": "0.7.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>The integration of Tailwind CSS framework with Django a.k.a. Django + Tailwind = \u2764</h1>\n<h2>Quick start</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Install the python package django-tailwind from pip</p>\n<p><code>pip install django-tailwind</code></p>\n<p>Alternatively, you can download or clone this repo and run <code>pip install -e .</code>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Add <code>tailwind</code> to INSTALLED_APPS in <strong>settings.py</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Create a tailwind-compatible Django-app, I like to call it <code>theme</code>:</p>\n<p><code>python manage.py tailwind init theme</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Add your newly created <code>theme</code> app to INSTALLED_APPS in <strong>settings.py</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>In settings.py, register tailwind app by adding the following string:</p>\n<p><code>TAILWIND_APP_NAME = 'theme'</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Run a command to install all necessary dependencies for tailwind css:</p>\n<p><code>python manage.py tailwind install</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Now, go and start tailwind in dev mode:</p>\n<p><code>python manage.py tailwind start</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Django Tailwind comes with a simple <code>base.html</code> template that can be found under\n<code>yourtailwindappname/templates/base.html</code>. You can always extend it or delete it if you\nhave own layout.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>If you're not using <code>base.html</code> template provided with Django Tailwind, add <code>styles.min.css</code> to your own <code>base.html</code> template file:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"p\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nt\">link</span>\n  <span class=\"na\">rel</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s\">\"stylesheet\"</span>\n  <span class=\"na\">href</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s\">\"{% static 'css/styles.min.css' %}\"</span>\n  <span class=\"na\">type</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s\">\"text/css\"</span>\n<span class=\"p\">/&gt;</span>\n</pre>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>You should now be able to use Tailwind CSS classes in your html.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>To build a production version of CSS run:</p>\n<p><code>python manage.py tailwind build</code>.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>NPM executable path configuration</h2>\n<p>Sometimes (especially on Windows), Python executable can't find <code>NPM</code> installed in the system.\nIn this case, you need to set <code>NPM</code> executable path in settings.py file manually (Linux/Mac):</p>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">NPM_BIN_PATH</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s1\">'/usr/local/bin/npm'</span>\n</pre>\n<p>On windows it might look like:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">NPM_BIN_PATH</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"sa\">r</span><span class=\"s2\">\"C:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\npm.cmd\"</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Please note that <code>NPM</code> path of your system may be different. Try to run <code>which npm</code> in your\ncommand line to get the path.</p>\n<h2>Bugs and suggestions</h2>\n<p>If you have found a bug, please use the issue tracker on GitHub.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/timonweb/django-tailwind/issues\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/timonweb/django-tailwind/issues</a></p>\n<p>2020 (c) <a href=\"https://timonweb.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">Tim Kamanin - A Full Stack Django Developer</a></p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6860271, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "6960819765385a60d5cc0c1299a3711d", "sha256": "28f4a61c61f11bb918626f1b461faa75ffdc4d4a23e472cbff9368b7a3041389"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "django-tailwind-0.0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "6960819765385a60d5cc0c1299a3711d", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 46264, "upload_time": "2019-04-11T19:53:01", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-04-11T19:53:01.231961Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/c4/da/ed13d3fb2973abeb5dde88c2912f7df86e83ec6197c8d42e0a05301153ef/django-tailwind-0.0.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "c2a2c528703e6f6a492c80d969ecde25", "sha256": "189dedad4b552a7bdd7733fc3286ccda8881f9cf7faa841e2b00f3b3e09a2729"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "django-tailwind-0.0.2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "c2a2c528703e6f6a492c80d969ec